    <Item class="ModuleScript" referent="110">
      <Properties>
        <string name="Name">How to Customize &amp; Presets!</string>
        <BinaryString name="AttributesSerialize"></BinaryString>
        <SecurityCapabilities name="Capabilities">0</SecurityCapabilities>
        <ContentId name="LinkedSource">
          <null>
          </null>
        </ContentId>
        <bool name="DefinesCapabilities">false</bool>
        <string name="Source">--[[

WHAT DO THESE PARAMETERS MEAN?
______________________________________________________________________________________________
• AltitudeOffset:						The altitude the atmosphere will display at sea level.
										(Good for minimizing floating point errors!)

• AtmosphereColor:						The color of the atmosphere.

• AtmosphereThickness:					The height of the atmosphere.

• AtmosphereTransparency:				How tenuous the atmosphere is.
										(Minimum 1x)

• AtmosphericExtinctionColor:			The color change that occurs during sunrise/sunset
										due to scattering of light.

• DistantSurfaceColor:					The color of the atmosphere 
										viewed from the horizon in space 
										or the color of the surface that 
										patches the 'draw distance' artifact.

• EnableAirglow: 						Enables the faint glow you see during the night
										which lies around the lower thermosphere (ionosphere)
										Note that you need to increase your exposure to see it.

	AirglowColor:							The color of the airglow.

	AirglowTransparency:					How faint the glow is.

• EnableApparentPlanetRotation: 		At high altitudes, the Earth appears to
										move under you when you're moving
										horizontally; good for when you're in orbit.

	InitialPlanetOrientation: 				The initial orientation of the planet when
											a player enters or respawns.

	EnableApparentSunMovement:				Synchronizes the Sun's position with the Earth
	(EXPERIMENTAL)							as you 'orbit' the Earth. NOTE: This feature is
											EXPERIMENTAL since it alters the game's time on
											the client's size only and has to reset to the
											server's time which might be altered by a
											Day and Night script that you may have placed.

											**FOR DAY/NIGHT CYCLES WITH THIS FEATURE CHECKED:
											Insert a NumberValue to the workspace and NAME
											IT: "ServerClockTime". That's your new clock 
											setting from then on. Redirect your day/night
											scripts to that value!


		EquatorialMovementOnly:					Disables the apparent Sun movement only when
												moving in a polar orbit. (Less buggy)

• EnableEnvironmentalLightingChanges:	Allows the script to change some lighting effects that
										would be recommended for the atmosphere.

	DaytimeSunlightColor:					The color of the Sunlight during the day.

	NightBrightness:						The lighting brightness during the night.

	OutdoorAmbientBrightnessDay:			The OutdoorAmbient shade during the day.

	OutdoorAmbientBrightnessNight:			The OutdoorAmbient shade during the night.

	SunlightBrightness:						The lighting brightness during the day.

	SunriseSunlightColor:					The color of the Sunlight when the Sun rises or sets.

• EnableGroundAtmosphere:				Makes the atmosphere from high altitudes visible in front
										of the ground. 

	GroundAtmosphereTransparency:			The transparency of the ground atmosphere.

• EnableMoon:							Enables the Moon.

	MoonApparentDiameter:					The apparent size of the Moon in arcseconds.

	MoonTexture: 							The texture of the Moon.

• EnableSun:							Enables the Sun.

	SunApparentDiameter:					The apparent size of the Sun in arcseconds.

	SunAtmosphericExtinctionColor:			The color change on the Sun itself as it rises or sets
											due to atmospheric scattering.

	SunBrightness:							How bright the rays appear around the Sun.

	SunTemp: 								The temperature of the Sun in degrees C which
											basically affects the color of the Sun.
	
	SunshineTexture:						The texture of the rays around the Sun.
					
• PlanetTexture:						The texture of the planet itself.

• PlanetTextureNight:					The texture of the planet during
										night time.

• Scale:								The scale of the planet and atmosphere
										in units of Earth multiples. 


//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

